			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yeah, it's true that this topic has been discussed, and discussed and discussed etc.
<br />

<br />
But, truthfully it has not been the same discussion.  Every time a new spell set comes out, or a whole new set of focus items, or AA's get added, or taken away, game mechanics get nerfed, or other changes happen, it changes the balance between which is a better choice for your play style.
<br />

<br />
So even if you had a solid answer before, the game changes, and suddenly you have reasons to go the other way.  Or more to the point, at least discuss if you should go the other way.  Thus... we keep seeing these threads.
<br />

<br />
It's actually a pretty dynamic issue with a lot of variables and personal preferences.  That's why it's never ended so easily.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b>Eandori
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760" target="_blank" class="postlink">"The pinnacle of pet offensive power can be achieved at level 50 with the epic pet. Does this make sense?"</a></span>
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
