				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would never ever use a lower nuke when i could use bigger nuke. Simple but that's how it is. If i wanted smaller nukes like SV i'd be a druid who have snare and heals. FBoT as it is now can hit anything even if mobs are aroud the corner, also i feel it has greater range too (not sure but it seems so).
<br />

<br />
You can do all the mana efficiency calculations you want, but this really is details when SV can crit for 3.5k and FBoT can crit for 4.4k, which means the dmg widens between those spells every time we have a critical hit. On that note, the greater the dmg focus, the more dmg one can gain with FBoT than SV (cause of the bigger base dmg of FBoT). OOW spells, even GREATER the gap...
<br />

<br />
As for rains, i use them a lot, i get many ae groups lately even in EP grouping. Rains are fun and its great to be ready to use them at all times and not using them is making the mage a more boring class, and i feel weird when i am in a group that i use rains and wizards dont, so pathetic. 
<br />

<br />
Burning Sand. With the latest version it's one of the most frequent spells i use right now, finally a nuke i can fit in at the final stages of a fight. So that's another factor.
<br />

<br />
Conjuration is not for me i can tell you that but also I dont think since secondary forte is around that specs make that much difference in the long run anyway, but still i am born to be a DPS nuker with a pet and not a conservative mage lol
<br />

<br />
So that's that...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
