			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">HeimSlush, 
<br />

<br />
If you really like the big bang of FoT, and the big crits.  Then that's great and all the power to you!  No matter what is the most efficient, highest DPS, etc.  If you have more fun playing a certain way, do that!  It's all about fun right?
<br />

<br />
As for me, I have a pretty good time casting FoT also.  I totally agree it's fun to land those big bangs and huge crits.  I don't use rains much anymore, and I don't have Burning Sand yet.  I would probably use Burning Sand on those raid mobs that die before I can get off a 6 second nuke.  
<br />

<br />
FoT absolutely does have a bigger range.  It's a LOT bigger too.  When my guild is fighting a raid mob with a big AoE, I can often back up out of his AoE range and still nuke him with FoT.  Pretty dang usefull when you can get mezzed, or nuked for 3k each cast.  Especially with Druzzils Distance FoT has huge range.
<br />

<br />
As a Conjurationist, I have lost none of my DPS potential.  I can cast Evocation just like an Evocationist.  I'm just a little less efficient when I do.  The extreme majority of my playstyle is all about efficientcy though, and I'm more efficient with Conjuration.
<br />

<br />
So that's that.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b>Eandori
<br />
