				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree 100% with you Ailees.
<br />

<br />
When I raid with tanks who generage massive aggro, I use FoT as long as it lands, and my mana pool holds out.  Most of the time it does, so I match DPS with evocationists and lose nothing.  Then when I go exp/solo etc. I'm more efficient so I end up doing more damage overall.
<br />

<br />
The only times I cannot match an evocationist is where Full DPS is needed, I run OOM before the fight is over, and Fire nukes land.  Which seems to be pretty rare for all 3 of those.  Most of the time, if I ran OOM, I would have ran OOM <span style="text-decoration: underline">anyways</span> because I ran OOM at like 30% mob HP left and being Evocation Specialized would have only given me 1-2 more nukes.  In those exact examples, if I had cast SV the whole time my mana pool would have stretched farther, so overall I did more damage.  Which is the end goal right?
<br />

<br />
Seems to me that saving mana over a 3 hour exp group is huge benefit to getting 1-2 more nukes in a small percentage of the raids for being evoc.  Besides all the other comparisons.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b>Eandori
